Key Insight (which the post explains very well):
If stress is uniform throughout the material, the forces cancel out and there is no net motion.
Motion or deformation only occurs when stress varies from one point to another.
The equation is derived by considering an arbitrary small volume inside the material, summing all forces acting on it (body forces + surface stresses), and requiring that the net force equals mass × acceleration.
